overview: The user wanted to improve the overall aesthetic of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which they felt was too generic. The assistant conducted a
  thorough review of the app's current visual design, identifying issues such as
  a generic color palette, plain backgrounds, dense form sections, and a lack of
  visual personality. The approach taken was to implement a comprehensive
  sleep-themed design. This involved updating the global CSS with a new calming
  color palette, redesigning the main questionnaire form with subtle background
  elements and improved card styling, enhancing the progress bar, and revamping
  the intro section with better visual hierarchy and feature cards.
  Additionally, form field components like checkboxes, radio buttons, and
  sliders were polished, and section groupings were updated for a more refined
  look. The report section also received a significant visual overhaul to align
  with the new theme, resulting in a more professional and inviting user
  interface.
